### Test Scenario
Test that bullet confidence decays over time as expected

### Test Steps

#### 1. No Decay at Creation
- Create bullet with confidence 0.9
- Immediately read effective confidence
- Verify effective = base confidence

#### 2. Decay After Half-Life
- Create bullet dated 30 days ago
- Default half-life = 30 days
- Verify effective confidence ~ 0.45 (half)

#### 3. Decay After Multiple Half-Lives
- Bullet dated 60 days ago (2 half-lives)
- Verify effective ~ 0.225 (quarter)
- Bullet dated 90 days ago (3 half-lives)
- Verify effective ~ 0.1125 (eighth)

#### 4. Decay Floor
- Very old bullet (1 year)
- Verify doesn't decay below floor (e.g., 0.01)
- Floor prevents total obsolescence

#### 5. Custom Half-Life
- Config: decay_half_life_days=7
- Bullet dated 7 days ago
- Verify effective = base * 0.5

#### 6. Decay Disabled
- Config: decay_enabled=false
- Old bullet
- Verify effective = base (no decay)

#### 7. Context Generation Impact
- Multiple bullets with different ages
- Generate context
- Verify newer bullets ranked higher
- Verify old bullets still included if relevant

